Aim:
To reverse the digits of a number.

Algorithm
Start
Input n
Initialize rev = 0
While n > 0
rev = rev Ã— 10 + (n % 10)
n = n / 10
Print rev
Stop

Program:
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;
int main(){
    int n, rev = 0;
    cout<<"Enter a number: ";
    cin>>n;

    while(n > 0){
        rev = rev*10 + n%10;
        n /= 10;
    }

    cout<<"Reversed Number = "<<rev;
    return 0;
}

Sample Output:
Enter a number: 9876
Reversed Number = 6789

Result:
The number is reversed successfully.
